### Hadith 4:373

*Narrated 'Amr bin Taghlib:*

Allah's Apostle gave (gifts) to some people to the exclusion of some
others. The latter seemed to be displeased by that. The Prophet said, "I
give to some people, lest they should deviate from True Faith or lose
patience, while I refer other people to the goodness and contentment
which Allah has put in their hearts, and 'Amr bin Taghlib is amongst
them." 'Amr bin Taghlib said, "The statement of Allah's Apostle is
dearer to me than red camels."

some property or some war prisoners and he distributed them in the above
way (i.e. giving to some people to the exclusion of others) .

